* [Sheep]: 23 Qty, 13 Value (Total: 299)

rounds.response:
My resources:
	+ [Wheat]   Qty: 25   Value: 6
	+ [Wood]    Qty: 9    Value: 10
	+ [Sheep]   Qty: 23   Value: 13
	+ [Brick]   Qty: 8    Value: 23
	+ [Ore]     Qty: 14   Value: 33

Player 1 rejected my previous offer. They also did not make an offer. This means they are not interested in gaining Wheat and Wood, or they want more valuable items than what I offered for the resources. I want to increase my Ore and Brick.

My strategy is to offer resources that I have in abundance and are low value (Wheat, Wood, Sheep), for high value resources (Ore, Brick). I have a lot of Sheep and Wheat, so I can offer those.

Offer: 15 Sheep, 10 Wheat -> 3 Ore, 2 Brick

Value of offered items: 15 * 13 (Sheep) + 10 * 6 (Wheat) = 195 + 60 = 255
Value of requested items: 3 * 33 (Ore) + 2 * 23 (Brick) = 99 + 46 = 145

This is a good offer for Player 1, as they would gain resources worth 255 for resources worth 145. I am still prioritizing increasing my Ore and Brick, even if it means giving up a higher value for now.

[Offer: 15 Sheep, 10 Wheat -> 3 Ore, 2 Brick]
